  "description": [
    "State House Beat FRANK LY SPEAKING By FRANK SMALL Back in 1848 Queen Victoria par doned the nine Irishmen sentenced to hang because of the intemperate re marks of one Thomas Francis Meagher who promised the judge My Lord this is our first offense but not our last If you will be easy with us this once we promise on our word as gentlemen to try and do better next time And next time sure we wont be fools enough to get caught In 1874 Victoria demanded in formation about the nine she had saved from being drawn and quart ered The astonishing list Thomas Francis Meagher Governor of Montana Terrence McManus brigadier gen eral U S Army Patrick Donahue brigadier gen eral U S Army Richard OGorman Governor Gen eral of Newfoundland Morris Lynne Attorney General of Australia in which office Michael Ireland succeeded him Thomas DArcy McGee Member of Parliament Montreal Minister of Agriculture and President of the Council Dominion of Canada John Mitchell prominent New York politician He was the father of John Purroy Mitchell mayor of New York at the outbreak of World War I Sure now dont be fool enough to be caught Tuesday Gov"
